"Yes, Vasilissa," spoke the guardian softly.  The guardian swiftly moved towards the hut to deliver the message.<br>
The smaller amazon strode into the barn and quickly outfitted one of her horses and then rode off towards the river in a steady cantor...giving herself still the time to think. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 391<br> <font color=#993300>(11/12/01 6:22:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gargensia Village</span><hr size=1>  Without the need of Marpe.. almost like it was telepathic. Dawn stood, and slipped silently out of the Queen's hut, giving a short nod to the guards on duty.<br>
<br>
 The amazon then slipped off to the side, immediately out of the village. She'd gotten used to the quiet of the forest and found it easier to track her way to the riverfront, than before, and easier without a horse.<br>
<br>
 Infact.. Dawn beat Hippolyte to the riverside. Her feet planting softly into the rocky side. She'd wait. <p>
