<br>
She looked to Dawn, her head slightly tilted to the side. "So...what do you think we should do?"  She wanted to hear an honest answer from those she would speak to.  Answers without any need to please the queen of Themiscrya.  Just honest...feelings and wisdom. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 398<br> <font color=#993300>(11/19/01 6:28:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gargarensia</span><hr size=1>  Dawn glancedat her, before taking a deep breath, her emeralds falling back to the muddy water of the river. Her hands gently folded behind her back, and her voice to follow gave only the chosen words and feelings of the assassin.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Take this as something strikingly odd, Hippolyte. I'm an assassin and one to love blood shed, and what I'm about to say..is going to strike you hard.&quot;<br>
<br>
 A hand behind her back moved abit before Dawn ended her silence, and started again.<br>
<br>
 &quot;This war is useless, and won't get us anything. It would be more of a regression for this tribe, and this nation than it would be anything else. If we fight those airhead men, it will be a loss to the ladies living there. They could leave if they wish, and they have not.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn paused once more, choosing her words again very wisely.<br>
<br>
 &quot;There are things in that village that would make amazons make sacrafices, choices they need not make. There are things there that are there for a retreat and could do US harm. I'm telling you no war. Its not needed, and not wanted.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Finally Dawn's eyes raised to meet Hippolytes, her face stern. This was the noble and wise Queen side of the Queen of Orio-Pata.<br>
